metadata.description:
Mono was your typical countryside cat. During one late-night prowl, Mono discovered The Hash. All the other cats were astonished by the beauty of the thrilling find. Not before long did all the cats find themself living in the vibrant New Hash City. To keep up with the constant adrenaline rush of their new life, the cats have developed several traits to help them master the city.

hash cats are a group of 512 generated cats with numerous different features.

Rarity features include:
â€“ 9 head colors
â€“ 32 different head-gears
â€“ 46 collars
â€“ 40 upper face traits (eyewear and makeup)
â€“ 3 lower face traits
â€“ 15 mouth and nose types
â€“ 46 sweaters and hoodies
â€“ 81 sweater traits
â€“ 3 gaze directions
â€“ 29 background patterns * 30 swatch variations
â€“ A very small chance to mint a cat with an artist signature

~ 1% chance to mint a Mono cat

hash cats is a collaboration GENTK by @levoontin & @3amkind.

Type 's' to save a PNG image of your cat (in full screen).

metadata.name: Tumble Down Light Factory #80
metadata.description:
Tumble Down Light Factory is an interpretation of light installations & murals.

It attempts to trigger the feeling of coming up on a new block in a new city to discover an unexpected piece of art that is stories tall or entering a new room, knowing there will be a projection dominating the space with its light and color.

This is an abstract distillation of those things and those feelings.

Each composition is initially drawn to a hidden â€œtemplateâ€ canvas which is sampled and then rendered on the main canvas in various ways after applying some transforms to give it some depth (and so you can actually see it.)

Viewing in full-screen is nice. You should try it.

T : Save hidden â€˜templateâ€™ image
S : Save current resolution
1 -> 5 : Save low -> high resolution

metadata.name: Laminar Dreaming #3
metadata.description:
While dreaming my octopus hug felt different, so, I kept on dreaming that I could bring it back whit me.
A noise odyssey that felt the laminar flow of the embrace, let us hug each other in synchronous harmony.
